name: std::backtrace::BacktraceStatus
doc_adt:
The current status of a backtrace, indicating whether it was captured or
 whether it is empty for some other reason.

VariantIdx(Some(0))-FieldIdx(None).name: Unsupported
VariantIdx(Some(0))-FieldIdx(None).doc:
Capturing a backtrace is not supported, likely because it's not
 implemented for the current platform.

VariantIdx(Some(1))-FieldIdx(None).name: Disabled
VariantIdx(Some(1))-FieldIdx(None).doc:
Capturing a backtrace has been disabled through either the
 `RUST_LIB_BACKTRACE` or `RUST_BACKTRACE` environment variables.

VariantIdx(Some(2))-FieldIdx(None).name: Captured
VariantIdx(Some(2))-FieldIdx(None).doc:
A backtrace has been captured and the `Backtrace` should print
 reasonable information when rendered.
